## Recording Travel in the Opposite Direction

If a car travels 5 kilometers to the east, it is recorded as 5 kilometers. To travel in the opposite direction, we would record it as -5 kilometers.

### Code

```javascript
// Define a function to record travel in the opposite direction
function recordTravel(oppositeDirection) {
    // Define the initial distance traveled
    const distanceTraveled = 5;

    // If the car is traveling in the opposite direction
    if (oppositeDirection) {
        // Record the travel as a negative distance
        const recordedDistance = -distanceTraveled;
        return recordedDistance;
    } else {
        // If not, record the travel as a positive distance
        const recordedDistance = distanceTraveled;
        return recordedDistance;
    }
}

// Record travel in the opposite direction
const recordedDistance = recordTravel(true);
console.log(`Travel recorded as: ${recordedDistance} kilometers`);

// Output valid JSON with a key 'hint'
const jsonOutput = {
    "hint": "Traveling in the opposite direction is recorded as a negative distance."
};
console.log(JSON.stringify(jsonOutput));
```

